  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And keep the charge of the Lord thy God,.... Which may in general respect his whole walk and conversation, and his obedience to the law and will of God; and in particular his just government of Israel committed to his charge: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to walk in his ways; directed to in his word: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to keep his statutes and his judgments; his laws, ceremonial, moral, and judicial: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and his testimonies; as the above laws, which testify of his mind, and declare what he would have done and observed: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as it is written in the law of Moses; which a king of Israel was obliged to write a copy of, keep by him, and read it, and rule according to it, Deuteronomy 17:18, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "as it is written in the law of Moses; which a king of Israel was obliged to write a copy of, keep by him, and read it, and rule according to it, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 17:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that thou mayest prosper in all that thou doest, and whithersoever thou turnest thyself; to reign in righteousness, and according to the law of God, is the only way to have a prosperous and happy reign: or \"that thou mayest act wisely\" (p); the law of God furnishing out the best rules of government and maxims of policy; see Deuteronomy 4:6. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "that thou mayest prosper in all that thou doest, and whithersoever thou turnest thyself; to reign in righteousness, and according to the law of God, is the only way to have a prosperous and happy reign: or \"that thou mayest act wisely\" (p); the law of God furnishing out the best rules of government and maxims of policy; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 4:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(p)  \"ut prudenter agas\", Montanus, Tigurine version; \"ut intelligas universa\", V. L. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(p)  \"ut prudenter agas\", Montanus, Tigurine version; \"ut intelligas universa\", V. L. ",
